HAMBURG SETS UP GENETIC TESTING LAB

HAMBURG - Hamburg in Germany has established a municipal laboratory for
the supervision of genetic engineering experiments.

Following the lead taken by Bavaria, Baden-Wurttemberg and Berlin,
Hamburg becomes the fourth state to open a laboratory of this kind. It
is the first, however, which is suitable to supervise experiments up to
the second highest security level (S3), according to the Hamburg
authorities.

"The new laboratory allows us to check whether researchers are actually
working with the genetically altered organisms they were given
permission for", said Fritz Vahrenholt, Hamburg's senator for the
environment.



