BIOTECHNOLOGY BUSINESS NEWS via NewsNet
January 17, 1996

CORVAS INTERNATIONAL RECEIVES $3 MILLION FROM SCHERING-PLOUGH

CORVAS INTERNATIONAL has received $3 million from Schering-Plough under
the companies' 1994 strategic alliance to develop and commercialise new
oral drugs for the prevention and treatment of chronic cardiovascular
disorders. Corvas will use the money to fund continuing activities
under the programme. To date, Corvas has received $13 million from the
agreement. If all future milestones are met and resulting products get
to market, Corvas could receive more than $80 million, plus royalties
on product sales.



