TOWA, CORTECS IN OSTEOPOROSIS PACT

Towa Pharmaceutical, a major manufacturer of generic drugs, has signed an
agreement with Cortecs International to co-develop an oral preparation of
salmon calcitonin (an osteoporosis remedy) currently under development by
the British company. The agreement gives Towa exclusive rights to
co-develop and market the oral preparation in Japan.
   At present, the oral preparation is undergoing Phase II clinical studies
in Europe. The drug will go on sale in Japan around the year 2005, with
sales estimated to reach some 10 billion yen at peak, according to Towa.
The company is already marketing an injectable formulation of salmon
calcitonin.

