CYCLIC NUCLEOTIDASE AND PROCESS FOR PRODUCING THE SAME.

EPO 682 109 A1 Published: November 15, 1995; Filed: January 28, 1994;
Priority: January 29, 1993
Taisho Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd., Tokyo (JP)
A novel cyclic nucleotidase which is of a type different from that of the
known isozyme family is isolated from rat's brain in pure form. It has
physicochemical properties such that (1) it acts upon cAMP to form 5'-AMP
and upon cGMP to form 5'-GMP; (2) in terms of substrate specificity, it has
a Km value of 0.11 M against cAMP and a Km value of 1.78 M against cGMP;
and (3) it has a molecular weight of about 298,000.

