BIOTECHNOLOGY NEWSWATCH via NewsNet
January 1, 1996   

A PROCESS FOR THE CLONING OF DNA.

EPO 683 238 A2 Published: November 22, 1995; Filed: July 18, 1989;
Priority: July 19, 1988
Nederlandse Organisatie voor toegepast-natuurwetenschappelijk onderzoek
TNO, The Hague (NL)
The invention relates to a process for the cloning of a DNA sequence
wherein a plasmid vector containing said DNA sequence is multiplied in
bacterial host which is incapable of host restriction, such as the
Escherichia coli C strain. The invention may be used for cloning DNA
sequences originating from a mammalian genome.

Copyright 1996 The McGraw-Hill Companies



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
