INTRODUCTION OF HIV-PROTECTIVE GENES INTO CELLS BY PARTICLE-MEDIATED GENE
TRANSFER.

WO 95/29703 Published: November 9, 1995; Filed: May 1, 1995; Priority:
April 29, 1994
Nabel, Gary, Ann Arbor, MI (US); Woffendin, Clive, Ann Arbor, MI (US);
Yang, Nin-Sun, Verona, WI (US); Sheehy, Michael J., Madison, WI (US)
Foreign genes may be stably introduced into T cells, monocytes,
macrophages, dendrites, and hematopoietic stem cells by particle-mediated
gene transfer. Introduction of an HIV protective gene into the cells of a
patient infected with HIV by particle-mediated gene transfer is effective
for the treatment of HIV infection.

