OPPORTUNITIES FOR SMALL COMPANY INNOVATIONS IN
BIOTECHNOLOGY

This work (by Bio-En-Gene-Er Associates) was undertaken
to help small businesses get on the fast track in
biotechnology research and development leading to the
spin-off of viable commercial businesses, probably with
the help of larger companies having the resources for
commercialization that are lacking in a small
enterprise.  Such resources could include financing and
positions in marketing, manufacturing, regulatory
affairs, and raw material supply.  In general,
biotechnology can be expected to have a major impact on
fundamental human needs engendered in the market
segments of: health care; agriculture; forestry; food
ingredients; industrial chemicals; plastics; energy;
mining; pollution control; and bioelectronics.

(Order this LIFE SCIENCES AND BIOTECHNOLOGY UPDATE
reviewed report from InfoTeam Inc., P.O. Box 15640,
Plantation, FL 33318-5640; Phone (954)/or(305)
473-9560, Fax (954)/or(305) 473-0544: Report No.
LD420R; Sep. 1993, 275 pp.  Price: $299.00, prepaid.)




