MOLTEN METAL SIGNS UP GERMAN SALES PARTNER

   A fledgling U.S. waste disposal firm has formed a strategic alliance to
market its proprietary catalytic extraction process to the worldwide
customers of a major German engineering and construction company.
   Waltham, Mass.-based Molten Metal Technology, Inc. has been a Wall St.
darling since the technology vendor went public in 1992. The company says
its closed-loop disposal system, which subjects industrial wastes to a
3000F molten metal bath, can recover acids and ferroalloys for recycling
while capturing harmful emissions.
   Dortmund-based Uhde GmbH became aware of Molten Metal through ``our
parent company, Hoechst AG,'' says Ulrike Kuske, vice president. Under
terms of the agreement, Uhde will identify and sell at least nine projects
based on Molten Metal's process over the next four years. Uhde's backlog
is $1.5 billion. Molten Metal just recorded its first profitable quarter.
William H. Haney III, president and CEO, expects to break even for the
year.

