Metropolitan Vladimir, who was one of two Russian Orthodox

Metropolitan Vladimir, who was one of two Russian Orthodox
observers at Vatican Council II, has been chosen to head the see
of St. Petersburg. He currently is metropolitan of Rostove and
Novocherkassk. As a young monk he attended Vatican II from its
opening day to the end.



