November 12, 1996

Albright and Wilson raises stake in Indian unit

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Chemicalweek Asia, 5 Nov 1996, Vol. 2, No. 19, Pg. 2

Albright and Wilson has increased its stake in Indian subsidiary
Albright, Moraji and Pandit (AMP) from 39% to 72%, making it majority
shareholder.

The additional shareholding has been purchased from Dharamsi Moraji
Chemical, which is now no longer a partner.

AMP has two facilities: it produces laundry detergents and technical
phosphates at Ambarnath and sulfuric acid and surfactants at Roha.

