Acrylonitrile process licensed in India

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Chemical Engineering Progress, Oct 1996, Vol. 92, No. 10, Pg. 28

The Indian Petrochemicals Corp Ltd, New Delhi, India is to build a
100,000 tonnes/y acrylonitrile plant in Jageshwar, Gujarat.

The plant will use BP Chemicals Inc's proprietary fluid bed
acrylonitrile process.

BP will also supply the catalyst for the plant which is scheduled to
come online in the year 2000.

