<A NAME = "25"></A>Copyright
CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE via NewsNet
November 12, 1996

Not a glitch in sight: GTC carboxylic acid recovery process

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Asia Pacific Chemicals, Nov 1996, Vol. 7, No. 9, Pg. 39

Glitsch Technology Corp (GTC), Houston, USA, has developed a process to
recover carboxylic acid products from waste water streams in dimethyl
terephthalate (DMT) plants.

Bombay Dyeing, India, with 200 tonnes/day of waste water is using the
process to reduce discharges and increase DMT capacity.

Acid levels as low as 1% in the water stream can be recovered and
purified to 99% for sale.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




