during the Seventh and Eight Five Year Plans (1985-1995) is discussed.

The main objectives for the Ninth Five Year Plan (1995-2000) are listed
and include achieving industrial output of RMB Yuan 1 bn by increasing
capacity to 150,000 tonnes carbon black, 40,000 tonnes caustic soda,
45,000 tonnes calcium carbide, 12,500 tonnes pesticide emulsifier, 7000
tonnes vinyl chloride acrylonitrile copolymer fibre, 13,000 tonnes
plexiglass, 4000 tonnes sodium cyanide, 5000 tonnes polyactylamide
latex and 2000 tonnes propylene alcohol ether.

Over 100 varieties of fine chemicals will be produced with fine
chemical production accounting for 50% of total output.

