from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: China Chemical Reporter, 16 Sep 1996, No. 28, Pg. 5

In 1995 total output of paper and paper board in China increased 12.2%
to 24,000 tonnes/y.

Imports are expected to rise by 8-10%/y from the current total of 3 M
tonnes.

By 2000 China intends to increase its capacity to 30 M tonnes/y with a
long term goal of 50 M tonnes/y.

In 1995 China's imports of paper pulp increased 1.8% to 824,000 tonnes.

Paper making capacity in China is to be increased by almost 10 M
tonnes/y over the next 5 years.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




