CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE via NewsNet
November 12, 1996

China to ban some chemical joint ventures

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Chemicalweek Asia, 5 Nov 1996, Vol. 2, No. 19, Pg. 5

China's chemical ministry intends to ban foreign investment in joint
ventures operating in pharmaceuticals, sodium carbonate, and sensitive
materials associated with the military, such as explosives.

But China will promote ventures or wholly owned foreign investments in
ethylene, fertilizers, fine chemicals, and fibres.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




