French insecticide market: conditions spur on growers to treat crops

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Circuits Culture, Oct 1996, No. Hors serie, Pg. 28-29

Original text in FRENCH

The French insecticide market saw an increase in activity in 1996
following several years of low insect infestation.

Growers have responded to the rise in insect attack by sowing Gaucho
treated seeds or by the use of pyrethroids.

A rise in the incidence of moths has resulted in a 6-10 fold increase
in pyrethroids.

The market leaders are the multi-purpose products Decis and Karate.
950,000 hectares of wheat and barley were treated with Gaucho.

