from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: European Chemical News, 4 Nov 1996, Vol. 66, No. 1739, Pg. 5

Exxon is to purchase Borealis's production facility for ethylene vinyl
acetate copolymer at Porvoo.

Borealis decided to sell the unit after finding that plans to expand
capacity were too expensive.

It also recognised that it was not well placed to take advantage of the
major potential markets, which are located in Asia.

Lear Corp has recently bought the Industrier operations from Borealis.

Exxon and Elf Atochem are the largest producers in Europe, where demand
is estimated at some 220,000 tonne/y.

The largest market is Germany, with the material being used for
production of high clarity film and hot melt adhesives.

