Maxim links with Exxon in CIS

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: European Rubber Journal, Nov 1996, Vol. 178, No. 10, Pg. 7

The Maxim Group is a new company formed from the remnants of the
Russian chemical industry.

It has major shareholdings in the Sintexkauchuk synthetic rubber plant
at Togliatti, which produces 35,000 tonnes/y of butyl rubber, 120,000
tonnes/y of E-SBR and 96,000 tonnes/y of stereoregular polyisoprene.

A related plant, the Orgsintez unit at Novomoskovsk, makes a variety of
