Combine, which is a leading supplier of raw materials and intermediates
to Russian chemical producers.

In addition, Maxim is involved in the production and marketing of
tyres, and is working with Exxon Chemical to improve the quality of its
tubeless tyres.

It has recently introduced a new range of tyres known as Forward,
designed especially for Russia's poor roads.

The tyres are said to match many foreign brands for performance, but
are cheaper.

Production will begin at two plants in the Ukraine in Oct 1996.

Maxim's total turnover in 1995 was $190 M.

