A 300 tonne/y laboratory scale unit has been built at Leverkusen, where
the new unit is also expected to be based.

Eventually, the company plans to build a 25,000-30,000 tonne/y
commercial facility.

Bayer's process involves the reaction of maleic anhydride and ammonia.

New technology, based on the polymerisation of aspartic acid, is being
jointly developed by Donlar, and Rohm and Haas.

Polyaspartic acids are used as sequestering and dispersing agents in
slurries and aqueous dispersions, and can prevent deposits building up
in boilers and cooling circuits.

Detergents used in extraction of petroleum can be softened and
dispersed using polyaspartic acids.

