November 12, 1996

BTR sells UK aero tyre division

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: European Rubber Journal, Nov 1996, Vol. 178, No. 10, Pg. 10

Dunlop Aircraft Tyres Ltd of the UK has been sold by its parent company
BTR to a European investment group led by 3I.

The price was #10 M ($15.6 M).

Dunlop Aircraft Tyres is based in Birmingham and has sales of #13 M/y
yielding profits of #1 M.

It employs 200 and is engaged in both manufacturing and retreading.

It supplies commercial and military markets with a range of over 300
products, most of them crossply.

It will retain the right to the Dunlop name, but it is not clear what
geographical markets this will apply to, as Sumitomo Rubber has the
right in some markets.

The Dunlop Aircraft Tyres plant at Birmingham has been upgraded with
investments totalling #4 M since 1994.

It is one of only four producers of aircraft tyres worldwide.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




