CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE via NewsNet
November 12, 1996

CARB proposes changes to VOC regulations

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: HAPPI, Household & Personal Products Industry, Oct 1996, Vol. 33, No.
10, Pg. 36

Amendments being proposed by the California Air Resources Board (CARB)
to its regulations regarding VOC emissions from consumer products and
aerosol coating products include: the redefinition of crawling bug and
flying bug insecticides; a new definition for hydrocarbons to mean any
of a class of compounds containing only hydrogen and carbon; a 25% VOC
limit for aerosol adhesives to be effective from 1 Jan 2002 and the
modification of the VOC definition to exclude perchloroethylene.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




