from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Handelsblatt Wirtschafts- und Finanzzeitung, 4 Nov 1996, Vol. 45, No.
213, Pg. 21

Original text in GERMAN

As part of necessary structural changes, Hoechst Trevira GmbH & Co KG
sees itself forced to close the Lenzing operations of Austria
Faserwerke GesmbH (AFW) by the end of 1996.

The shift of the textile industry to the Far East, pressure from cheap
imports and overcapacity have necessitated the decision.

Hoechst Trevira has posted losses in the sector. 110 employees are
effected.

Hoechst Trevira produces staple fibres at 4 plants and had turnover in
the sector of DM 393 M in 1995, AFW accounting for DM 65 M.

Hoechst Trevira had turnover of DM 2.27 bn in W Europe in 1995.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




