tonnes/y by 2000; Sao Paulo, with capacity of 460,000 tonnes/y; Triunfo
(Rio Grande do Sul) with capacity of 685,000 tonnes/y, rising to 1.135
M tonnes/y by 1998; and Bahia Blanca (Argentina), with capacity of
250,000 tonnes/y, rising to 330,000 tonnes/y by 1998.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




