November 12, 1996

Granitol commissions new technology

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Hospodarske Noviny, 7 Nov 1996, Vol. 40, No. 218, Pg. 6

Original text in CZECH

Granitol, Czech Republic, a manufacturer of polyethylene packaging
foils, has commissioned a new line.

The line allows two-colour printing on palletisation foils.

Granitol bought the line for DM 1.6 M (about CEK 32 M).

In 1995 the investment went into two blow-moulding lines with a
printing machine and into an automatic welding line for bags and
carriers.

The company invested the most of its 1995 net profit, which totalled
CEK 2.1 M.

Granitol saw a net profit of CEK 18.7 M in 1994.

The company's turnover rose by 37% to CEK 722 M in 1995 compared to
1994.

The firm has a stock of CEK 265.5 M.

