capacity for 150,000 tonnes/y plus a 23,000 tonnes/y emulsion plant, is
to expand its PVC capacity by 120,000 tonnes/y in 1998 with privileges
granted by the Thai Board of Investment (a tax holiday for 7 years
followed by tax at 50% of the usual rate for the following 5 years).

A 100,000 tonnes/y PVC plant is to be built by Apex Plastics which will
use 60% of its output in house.

Thai demand for PVC is expected to rise by 16% in 1996 to 417,000
tonnes followed by 12% growth to 2000. 50% of demand is for pipes and
profiles.

