<A NAME = "602"></A>Copyright
CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE via NewsNet
November 12, 1996

UK reviews of mecoprop and mecoprop-P: amendment to the conditions of
approval

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: The Pesticides Register, Oct 1996, No. 10, Pg. 2

Product labels specifying the conditions of approval for mecoprop and
mecoprop-P in the UK must now be amended following a review of these
active ingredients.

So that mecoprop and mecoprop-P products are consistently labelled
during the transitional period from the mixed to the single isomer
review label amendments will be imposed on the both mecoprop and
mecoprop-P.

The deadline established for implementation of the label changes should
mean that existing mecoprop product labels can remain for the final
season of use before the deadline for applications for the transition
of mecoprop-P.

The label amendments must be incorporated for any mecoprop or
mecoprop-P containing product entering the supply chain 12 months after
the implementation date.

