EPA requires additional precautionary labelling for pet pesticides

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Pesticide and Toxic Chemical News, 23 Oct 1996, Vol. 24, No. 52, Pg.
18-19

Under EPA's (Environmental Protection Agency) new PR-Notice 96-6
manufacturers of pet pesticides registered for use on dogs and cats
must add further details to their labels.

Information needed includes the species, age and condition of the pet
along with any adverse properties and cholinesterase-inhibiting
characteristics of the product.

First-aid information and a contact telephone number of an Animal
Poison Control Centre or company to be reached in emergencies are also
required.

