The Grocery Manufacturers of America believes that the Act will result
in the development of more biopesticides and plants genetically
engineered for pest resistance.

It expressed concern at the politicization of pesticide residues and
the level of civil penalties against food processors who violate
pesticide residue tolerances.

Further concern was the oestrogenic and cumulative effects of
pesticides.

The view was expressed that FQPA would encourage the employment of
minor use pesticides to the benefit of the food industry.

The Food Chain Coalition is to monitor implementation of FQPA and
encourage congressional interest as a means of retaining pesticides.

