Amoco unit feels heat to supply hot PAN: carbon fibre demand tight

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Plastics News, 23 Sep 1996, Vol. 8, No. 30, Pg. 11

Demand for carbon fibre for aerospace applications is growing rapidly,
led by an increase in the construction rate of commercial aircraft by
Boeing Co.

This has led to a shortage of supply.

Almost all of the output from Amoco Performance Products Inc's 2.2 M
lb/y PAN-based carbon fibre production capacity in Greenville, SC, is
for aerospace applications.

By 1997, availability of carbon fibre for sporting applications would
also be difficult, but there are a number of planned production
increases which should ease this situation.

Toray Industries Inc, Toho Rayon Co, Zoltek Cos Inc, Akzo Nobel NV and
RK International Ltd are all planning to raise capacity.

By the end of 1997, Amoco Performance Products plans to achieve full
capacity of 2 M lb/y at its facility in Rock Hill, SC.

The unit is undergoing refurbishment and debottlenecking.

Capacity amounting to 1 M lb/y was brought back onstream in late 1995.

