production lines for flexible PP film at Battipaglia in Italy.

The line cost over $30 M and can produce 24,000 tonnes/y of PP film at
a speed of 320 metres/min.

It can also produce monolayer or coextruded film with thicknesses of
between 15 and 50 microns.

The new line brings Moplefan's production capacity to 122,000 tonnes/y,
confirming it as a leading player in the European flexible packaging
market.

It has two sites in Italy, one in Belgium and one in the UK.

