operate at 85% capacity in 1997.

Equipment will be moved from the site to Continental Barum SRO, based
at Otrokovice, Czech Republic.

The company is increasing capacity at this site by 50%.

When Austria joined the European Union, the demand for its tyres from
Japanese car manufacturers disappeared.

Production will be increased at Traiskirchen if suitable contracts can
be negotiated.

