New technology developed by BASF AG, which holds 49% of the joint
venture with Tongyang Nylon Co Ltd, will be used for the expansion.

The new economical process, which uses less water for emulsions, is
being installed at Ludwigshafen, where BASF is to increase ABS capacity
to 418 M lb/y from Sep 1997.

The unit also produces other styrene copolymers.

In 2Q 1998, a 300 M lb/y facility for production of speciality styrene
copolymers is due to be brought onstream in Altamira, Mexico, by BASF.

Output will be supplied to customers in North America.

