<A NAME = "741"></A>Copyright
CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE via NewsNet
November 12, 1996

Fina line to bolster PS supply

from CHEMICAL BUSINESS NEWSBASE, 12 Nov 1996

Ref: Plastics News, 30 Sep 1996, Vol. 8, No. 31, Pg. 3

In Sep 1996, production was started by Fina Oil and Chemical Co at a
new $39 M, 125,000 lb/y crystal polystyrene unit at Carville, LA,
increasing capacity at the facility to 1.03 bn lb/y and making the
company the second largest US producer.

The facility is now claimed to be the largest of its kind worldwide.

In 1994, PS capacity utilization rose to 91% in response to strong
demand.

Demand is still strong, although operating rates have declined slightly
to 88-89%.

Copyright 1996 Royal Society of Chemistry




