SCIENTISTS MAP AN ENZYME TO DESTROY PCBS

Purdue University researchers last month mapped the three-dimensional
structure of extradiol dioxygenase, which initiates a critical step in
breaking down many polychlorinated biphenyls. The enzyme is found in
Pseudomonas cepacia. For more information, Jeffrey Bolin can be reached at
the e-mail address: jtb@mace.cc.purdue.edu.

