DOW FORMS A CONTRACT- MANUFACTURING BUSINESS

Dow Chemical Co. (Midland, Mich.) has formed a new business, Contract
Manufacturing Services, to help customers cut the time needed to bring a
product to commercialization. The business is aiming for companies that
have developed new molecules, but cannot afford the inhouse capabilities
and facilities needed for process development and manufacturing. ``We can
provide process development capabilities, manufacturing experience in both
large- and small-volume chemical production, facilities for contract
manufacturing, and toxicological knowledge,'' says Maggi Walker, business
director for the new company.

