`SOFT SKILLS' ARE CRITICAL, SURVEY FINDS

December graduates who can comfortably hold a conversation should have an
edge in the job market, according to a recent survey of employers by the
National Association of Colleges and Employers (Bethlehem, Pa.). Oral
communication, interpersonal and teamwork skills ranked first among
employers, whereas proficiency in field came in eighth, and computer
skills, ninth.

