January 1996   Vol. 103, No. 

AUDIT POLICY SET BY EPA

Last month, EPA finalized its environmental audit policy to protect
companies that operate in good faith, while rejecting ``privilege and
immunity'' laws for polluters. The move won praise from the Environmental
Defense Fund (Washington, D.C.) ``The policy provides responsible companies
a reliable break in penalties without letting scofflaws off the hook,''
says EDF policy analyst Carol Andress.

