FIBERGLASS-REINFORCED LINING RESISTS ATTACK

Resisting thermal shock, thermal cycling, static cracks and permeation,
this fiberglass reinforcing mat can be used with novolac, polyester and
vinyl ester resin systems. The complete system consists of a glass-filled
mortar, a permeating saturant, and a mineral composite topcoat. Used to
protect concrete tanks, trenches, floors, pits and tank pads, the lining
resists attack by concentrated sulfuric acid, chlorinated solvents and
caustics.--Stonhard, Inc., Maple Shade, N.J.

